//Write a function to find GCD of two numbers.

jshell> public class Functions{
   ...>     public static int gcdOfTwo(int m , int n){
   ...>         while(m != n){
   ...>             if(m >n)
   ...>             m = m-n;
   ...>             else
   ...>             n = n-m;
   ...>         }
   ...>         return m;
   ...>     }
   ...>     public static void main(String []args){
   ...>         Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
   ...>         int m = sc.nextInt();
   ...>         int n = sc.nextInt();
   ...>
   ...>         System.out.println(gcdOfTwo(m,n));
   ...>     }
   ...> }
Output:
|  modified class Functions

jshell> Functions.gcdOfTwo(2,5);

//Fibonacci series upto n terms
 public class Functions{
   ...>     public static void fiboSeries(int n){
   ...>         int a =0, b = 1, c;
   ...>
   ...>     System.out.print( a +","+b);
   ...>
   ...>        for(int i = 0 ;i <n-2; i++){
   ...>             c = a +b;
   ...>             a=b;
   ...>             b=c;
   ...> System.out.print("," + c);        }
   ...>
   ...>
   ...>         }
   ...>     public static void main(String []args){
   ...>         Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
   ...>         int n = sc.nextInt();
   ...>
   ...>        fiboSeries(n);
   ...>     }
   ...> }
Output:
|  modified class Functions

jshell>  Functions. fiboSeries(5);
0,1,1,2,3
$5 ==> 1

jshell> Functions.gcdOfTwo(2,2);
$6 ==> 2


Q.Write a program to enter the numbers till the user wants and at the end it should display the count of positive, negative and zeros entered. :
Code:
public class NumberCounter{
        public static void countNumbers(){
            Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
            int positive  = 0, negative = 0, zero = 0;
           char choice;
   ...>
            do{
                System.out.print("Enter a number: ");
                int num = sc.nextInt();
   
                if(num > 0) positive++;
                else if(num < 0) negative++;
                else zero++;
   
   ...>             System.out.print("Do you  want to enter another number?(
y/n): ");
   ...>             choice = sc.next().charAt(0);
   ...>         }
            while(choice == 'y' || choice == 'Y');

             System.out.println("Positive Numbers: "+ positive);
 System.out.println("Negative Numbers: "+ negative);
 System.out.println("Zeros: "+ zero);


   ...>     }
   ...>     public static void main(String []args){
   ...>         countNumbers();  // call  the  function
   ...>     }
   ...> }
